'''Whyte's francolin''' ('''''Scleroptila whytei''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Phasianidae]].  It is found in grassy woodlands and grasslands in [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[Malawi]], and [[Zambia]].

